’Щ@34dbf53a7134e24e1854671081120655f4c29e54738d3637ca05a7d8d14bebccЪхTitle: title: path dirname
Path: Examples
Content:
Get dirname of a path.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '/home/joe/code/test.txt' | path dirname
/home/joe/code

```
Get dirname of a list of paths.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [ /home/joe/test.txt, /home/doe/test.txt ] | path dirname
в•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®
в”‚ 0 в”‚ /home/joe в”‚
в”‚ 1 в”‚ /home/doe в”‚
в•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”ґв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї


```
Walk up two levels.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '/home/joe/code/test.txt' | path dirname --num-levels 2
/home/joe

```
Replace the part that would be returned with a custom path.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '/home/joe/code/test.txt' | path dirname --num-levels 2 --replace /home/viking
/home/viking/code/test.txt

```
